1
00:00:03,031 --> 00:00:04,833
In Vienna, two maternity wards sat under

2
00:00:04,833 --> 00:00:06,636
one hospital roof.

3
00:00:07,397 --> 00:00:08,549
The first clinic was run by doctors

4
00:00:08,549 --> 00:00:09,700
and students.

5
00:00:10,602 --> 00:00:12,144
The second was run by midwives.

6
00:00:12,926 --> 00:00:14,087
The patients were similar.

7
00:00:14,868 --> 00:00:16,111
The death rates were not.

8
00:00:17,071 --> 00:00:19,756
By 1846, the first clinic was losing

9
00:00:19,756 --> 00:00:22,440
more than one in ten mothers.

10
00:00:22,420 --> 00:00:24,202
Across the same years, the second stayed

11
00:00:24,202 --> 00:00:25,984
under 4%.

12
00:00:26,846 --> 00:00:28,989
Semmelweis found the difference in the routine.

13
00:00:29,048 --> 00:00:32,023
Doctors moved from autopsies to childbirth without

14
00:00:32,023 --> 00:00:34,998
effective disinfection.

15
00:00:35,819 --> 00:00:38,442
He required chloride of lime hand disinfection.

16
00:00:39,463 --> 00:00:40,384
Mortality fell.

17
00:00:41,447 --> 00:00:42,919
The evidence worked before germ theory could

18
00:00:42,919 --> 00:00:44,390
explain why.

19
00:00:44,411 --> 00:00:46,774
That was the problem.

20
00:00:46,753 --> 00:00:48,367
Believing the data meant believing doctors had

21
00:00:48,367 --> 00:00:49,980
been carrying death from the dead to

22
00:00:49,980 --> 00:00:51,594
the living.

23
00:00:51,634 --> 00:00:53,944
The institution protected its identity longer than

24
00:00:53,944 --> 00:00:56,253
it protected the evidence.

25
00:00:57,078 --> 00:01:00,392
Small causes, massive consequences.
